sentences: Miwa Sasagawa (笹川 美和, Sasagawa Miwa, born February 23, 1983) is a Japanese singer-songwriter.
Miwa was born in Shiunji, Niigata (currently Shibata) and graduated from Niigata Woman's College.
In 2000, her original song "Thanks to be here" won the grand prize at the Mos Burger-sponsored Christmas Song Grand Prix.

On September 18, 2003 her major label debut single "Warai" was released by avex trax.
Her single "Shiunji" (紫雲寺) ranked on the Oricon charts despite being a 2000-copy limited edition available only in Niigata Prefecture.
Her contract with Avex Group expired at the end of July 2007.

She continued on as in independent artist after that but in 2012 a new official website appeared on the Avex portal and it was announced she had re-signed with Avex after a 5-year hiatus and that new releases were forthcoming.
